From 521914882b704aff4af7d51a6a75956bb8018fe2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Aug 2025 08:39:22 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:hostapd: ATF: ssid specific configurations

This patch introduces new CLI commands to manage SSID-level
airtime configuration.
The following operations are added:

- Configure SSID scheduling policy.
- Add a new SSID with airtime configuration.
- Modify existing SSID scheduling parameters.
- Delete a configured SSID.
- Display all configured SSIDs.

cli commands:
MLO:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload atfssidsched <1/0>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload addssid  <ssidname>
<airtime %>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload delssid   <ssidname>
Legacy:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload atfssidsched <1/0>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload addssid <ssidname>
<airtime %>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload delssid <ssidname>

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
